 9 Intelligence

Weight: 1~


//Nahal's Reckless Dweomer
@60053 = ~Wand of Nahal's Reckless Dweomer~
@60054 = ~The Wild Mage's ultimate last-resort, a wild surge is purposefully invoked; the result might be beneficial to the Mage, or it might be completely disastrous: this is the risk the Wild Mage takes in casting Nahal's Reckless Dweomer.

When activated, select a known spell to attempt to cast; the wand releases a sudden flood of wild magical energy. The Wild Mage hopes to seize and shape that energy into a desired spell effect. The attempt usually fails, but something almost always occurs in the process -- the actual effect of the wand is determined randomly by a dice roll on the Wild Surge Table (see the manual for more details).

Because the release of energy is planned, the wand's caster level (%magnitude%) is added to the dice roll. If the result indicates success, the Mage has shaped the magical energy into the desired effect. More often than not, the effect is completely unexpected.

STATISTICS:
(Invocation/Evocation)

Charge abilities:
– Nahal's Reckless Dweomer
  Pick a known spell; wild surge occurs that attempts to cast the selected spell
  Range: Special
  Area of Effect: Special
  Duration: Special
  Saving Throw: Special

Requires:
 9 Intelligence

Weight: 1~


//Spook
@60055 = ~Wand of Spook~
@60056 = ~This wand's effect plays upon natural fears to cause the target creature to perceive the wielder as someone or something inimical, which then appears to advance upon it in a threatening manner. If the creature does not make a successful save vs. Wand, it turns and flees at maximum speed as far from the wielder as possible. Undead are completely unaffected.

